node.title: Jetstar pilot remains in custody as police work to solve missing campers case
node.alt: A split image showing an older, bald man on the left and an older, smiling woman on the right.
node.description: Police arrest and interview 55-year-old pilot Greg LynnÂ and examine his 4WD for forensic evidence as they investigate the disappearance of Russell Hill and Carol Clay in Victoria's remote high country in March last year.
node.content:
["A Jetstar employee remains in police custody over the disappearance of Victorian campers Russell Hill and Carol Clay, who went missing more than 20 months ago.", "The couple\u00a0were last heard from on March 20, 2020, from their remote Wonnangatta Valley campsite in the Victorian high country.", "The campsite was later found burnt out, but Mr Hill's four-wheel drive was still there.", "For several months, detectives have appealed for information as they used interviews and CCTV cameras in an attempt to identify all the cars that were in the valley at the time and track down the owners one by one.", "On Monday night, special operations officers descended on a campsite near Moroka Road at Arbuckle Junction, roughly 55 kilometres south of the Wonnangatta Valley.", "The officers arrested 55-year-old Greg Lynn\u00a0from Caroline Springs and seized his Nissan Patrol for forensic testing.", "Last night, Jetstar\u00a0Airways confirmed\u00a0Mr Lynn\u00a0was a pilot who worked\u00a0for the airline, and that he had been stood down from his position.", "", "
This taupe-coloured Nissan Patrol was towed into the Victoria Police Forensic Services Centre in Melbourne's north-east last night.(ABC News)
", "He remains in police custody and is being questioned at Sale Police Station.", "No charges have been laid against him.", "It is the first arrest that has been made by officers investigating the case."]
